rComments: Professor is clear and easy to listen to, but the lectures tend to drone on for a while. Recommended to watch them at 1.5x-2x speed. Very reading heavy, 50+ pages of reading required per week, and you WILL be tested on them during the exam. 2 hours of lecture every week, + an hour of tutorial, standard stuff. TAs very anal about the essays.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: She's an okay professor, not my favourite but the course itself is not a bird course! There are about 50 pages of reading each week for reading quizzes and every one of those readings is critical for your final exam. Its also lectures recorded but she talks so much. TA marks the 2 essays in between so hard, you better be basically an English major.
teacherRatingTags: ['Participation matters', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: I would say the course material alone is pretty interesting compared to the other available subjects... HOWEVER, do not take this class if you're looking to breeze by with a high grade. She speaks pretty casually which makes the lectures more engaging and comprehensive to students, but there is so much tedious work that goes into your grade.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: If you enjoy reading the most boring articles, this is the course for you. Sarah is a kind and funny prof but the course itself is horrible. Do not make the mistake that I did - thinking that ggr107 is a bird course. It's not.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Get ready to read', 'Tough grader']

rComments: horrible and marks hard
HARD,LONG, and COMPLICATED READINGS ALONG THE SEMESTER. TRY TO GET AWAY FROM HER AS FAR AS POSSIBLE

Im so happy I took this course, Sarah is wonderful. Her sense of humour made the heavier/dryer material easier to get through! Shes passionate about what she teaches and is super knowledgeable. There is a HEAVY amount of required reading, some of which I think couldve been substituted with documentary footage, which could be more impactful.

She was super passionate about the subject matter which in my opinion is the most important trait of a good prof. Her enthusiasm made the course really engaging. The course is reading heavy but there is still a lot of info given in lecture.

She is very knowledgable and has great ability in conveying the material clearly. Slides and lecture audio are posted on the Q, so they're easily accessible and organized. There are quite a lot of readings to do so you got to stay on top of things! Overall a pleasant experience.
- excellent critical writing skill required - lectures are not attractive - no textbook required
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: EXTREMELY BORING COURSE! DO NOT TAKE IT! Contents, lectures, and tutorials gives me no interest. I am wondering why we have this such boring and meaningless course in UofT...

Prof Wakefield is fantastic and really knows her material, she is extremely organized and posted not only all lecture slides but audio with them! She is very good at providing visual aids. Only complaint the course was very reading heavy with associated quizzes!All in all Very caring and kind prof!

rComments: Class has a lot of reading associated with it. Class was alright but a bit boring.

rComments: They changed prof in 2015. She is a new prof and super boring. Most students can't got her point when she's talking. I like what I learned by myself but I totally don't like her

Very kind and genuine person who cares about the material and gives well organized enjoyable lectures. Some of the material is a bit drab, but she moves at the right pace and spends more time on interesting material. Good TA as well.

I found this class pretty boring and easy, but thats probably because i've studied the material before. Otherwise, the prof is super approachable and friendly. I wasn't enrolled in a tutorial and she let me choose whichever one suited my timetable even though it was full!
Loved this class! Professor Wakefield was approachable, helpful and made lectures engaging.
Great pro with high clarification on the materials! Interesting lectures and attractive personality :)
Awesome prof! Really easy to follow her lectures, assignments were straightforward not too too heavy. Definitely recommend
Great course, great professor!

Nice,attentive and approachable.She has a certain perspective on things and tends to follow it in course material, but she tells you this in first class. Going along will make life easier, but if you can convince her otherwise she'll give you the mark. Lecute and notes are clear & organized, summary of text,so READ & remember her examples!
smart. funny. innovative.  a great prof.  i only wish the class had not been group-based. group projects are so lame and unrealistic, and they kill creativity.  great prof tho, like i said.
pretty easy class, not much effort needed, and the content was interesting as well. Wakefield is also nice and approachable.

this course is the MOST BIASED course I have taken in my university career. NOT recommended. Perhaps the professor and TA's should criticize themselves for being biased, rather than critically appraising other people's work for biased point of view. SERIOUSLY...
Does not understand the students. Yells at students in class. Very closed-minded. Doesn't depend on your TA at all because the TA's all mark with her.
nice professor, but the TA is VERY harsh at marking. hard to get good marks because the assignments worth total 60% of marks.
Great teacher, young, energetic, passionate, and from what I experienced she actually cares about her students!

Wakefield is really a kind and friendly lady.  Her intentions are genuinely good in teaching the course, but at times she can be a bit unclear.  She has a tendency to digress from the main topic a bit, and some of her lectures can get a bit tedious.  Nonetheless, she's very open to discussion and approachable.

great attitude - wonderful prof. who cares about what she teaches and tries to engage students into that field - very interesting and fun personality when she lectures! :) actually interesing and "fun" class assignments!
If only she would learn to be clear about what she's saying. Shes so great otherwise!!

Really, really helpful. Besides making enironmental studies interesting and informative, she also taught me more fundamental basics on how to write an essay and how to read academic work. She's a wonderful prof.
